ailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/19\/wudu-salat-expiate-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Salah: Excellent ablution, prayer erases minor sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 19, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"No Muslim attends a prescribed prayer and performs its ablution, reverence, and bowing in the best manner, but that it will be an expiation for his previous sins as long as he did not commit\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33003,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/perfect-wudu-five-salawat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Perfect ablution, five prayers expiation of sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever perfects his ablution as Allah Almighty has commanded him, the prescribed prayers will be an expiation for what occurs between them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 231 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u062b\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2787,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/06\/wudu-perfect-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Description of a perfect ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 6, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Humran reported: Uthman, may Allah be pleased with him, requested a vessel of water and he poured water over his hands three times and washed them. Then, he put his right hand in the vessel and rinsed his mouth and sniffed water into his nose. Then, he washed his face\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":309,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/04\/the-virtue-of-ablution-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Ablution is radiance on Judgment Day","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 4, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira\u00a0reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Verily, my nation will be called on the Day of Resurrection as brightly radiant from the traces of ablution. Whoever among you is able to extend his radiance, let him do so.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 136, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13995,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/06\/every-step-mosque-rewarded\/","url_meta":{"origin":14001,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Mosques: Every step to mosque for prayer is rewarded","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever purifies himself with ablution in his house, then he walks to a house among the houses of Allah to fulfill an obligation among the obligations of Allah, one step of his will expiate his sins\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/14001","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/us